<h2><strong>What Is a Wedding Guest List App?</strong></h2>
<p>A wedding guest list app is a web or mobile tool that centralizes guest names, contact info, guests information, guest info, RSVP status, plus-ones, and special notes in one place. Unlike static Excel files or Google Sheets, an app updates in real time as guests respond and can sync with digital invitations and your wedding website.</p>
<p>These apps typically live on browser-based dashboards for desktop planning, native iOS and Android apps for on-the-go access, or integrated tools within broader wedding planning platforms. eydn combines guest list management with the rest of your wedding — budget, checklist, vendors, and website — so everything stays connected rather than siloed. Top apps for managing a wedding guest list, such as Zola, The Knot, and WeddingWire, offer a free guest list manager to track RSVPs, collect addresses, and organize seating charts across devices. A guest list template can help organize guests information and guest info in one place for every event, and many guest list managers allow users to track RSVPs and meal choices in one convenient location. Guest list templates can include columns for dietary restrictions and allergies.</p>
