<h2><strong>Common Guest List Mistakes</strong></h2>
<p>Even the most organized couples can fall into common guest list mistakes during wedding planning. One frequent error is booking the venue before finalizing the guest list, which can lead to last-minute changes, stress, and even exceeding the venue’s capacity. Always confirm your guest count before signing any contracts.</p>
<p>Another pitfall is failing to communicate important details—like plus-one policies or RSVP deadlines—clearly to your guests. This can result in confusion, missed responses, and unnecessary follow-ups. Over-inviting is another common mistake that can quickly blow your wedding budget and make the event feel overwhelming.</p>
<p>To avoid these issues, take time to plan your guest list carefully, set clear expectations, and keep your guests informed throughout the process. Staying organized and proactive will help you manage your guest count, stick to your budget, and create a seamless experience for everyone on your big day.</p>
