<p><strong>When should we start using digital wedding planning tools?</strong> Begin setting up core tools — email, shared drive, basic guest list, and budget sheet — as soon as you set a target date, ideally 12–18 months before the wedding. Vendor search tools, seating charts, and detailed timelines become most useful six to nine months out when logistics solidify.</p>
<p><strong>How many wedding planning tools do we really need?</strong> A lean stack works best: one all-in-one planner or wedding website, one collaboration suite, one task manager, and one budget tool. If that still sounds like a lot to manage, Eydn brings the essentials together in a single app — no assembly required.</p>
<p><strong>Are free tools enough, or should we pay for premium plans?</strong> Many couples successfully plan using only free tiers. Consider paid plans only when they unlock specific features you genuinely need — custom domains, extra photo storage, advanced floor plans, or ad-free guest experiences.</p>
<p><strong>How do we keep our wedding data private and secure?</strong> Use strong, unique passwords and enable two-factor authentication for any tools containing contracts or financial data. Review privacy settings on your wedding website and restrict access to sensitive documents to only those who genuinely need them.</p>
<p><strong>What if one of us isn''t very tech-savvy?</strong> Choose tools with simple, intuitive interfaces. Designate one person as "primary admin" while maintaining shared access, and document key how-tos in a simple shared note for easy reference. eydn is designed to be conversational — if you''re not sure what to do next, you can just ask.</p>',
